    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/627: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-02T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 2, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s instruction No. 346 of April 16 and Legation’s telegram 62 of
                    April 19. Navy Department has arranged to retain Colonel <persName
                        corresp="#p_MMGCB1">Matthews</persName> in command of the Guardia until
                    American officers are withdrawn. Please so inform Nicaraguan Government in reply
                    to its note of April 1, 1932.<note n="57" xml:id="d876fn57">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Express to Colonel <persName corresp="#p_MMGCB1">Matthews</persName> the
                    Department’s appreciation for his sacrifice and cooperation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
